.TH "of_reset_simple_xlate" 9 "of_reset_simple_xlate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_reset_simple_xlate \- translate reset_spec to the reset line number
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_reset_simple_xlate
.BI "(struct reset_controller_dev *rcdev "  ","
.BI "const struct of_phandle_args *reset_spec "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rcdev" 12
a pointer to the reset controller device
.IP "reset_spec" 12
reset line specifier as found in the device tree
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This static translation function is used by default if of_xlate in
:c:type:`reset_controller_dev` is not set. It is useful for all reset
controllers with 1:1 mapping, where reset lines can be indexed by number
without gaps.
